story.title: The Red Room - Episode 2
story.storyDescription: Ashley and Mark are in terrible danger. Can they both survive the terrors of the Red Room?
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Michael Ojunga is a Los Angeles based fiction writer. Follow him to read more stories like “The Red Room”.

story.prePaywallNotification: How can Mark possibly be outside Ashley’s house? It’s related to the THE RED ROOM. Keep reading.
story.postPaywallNotification: Can Mark survive and save Ashley? Read more of THE RED ROOM.

messages.text: Wait, you’re outside my house??
How did you get here so fast?
I’m not exactly sure.
The guy at the frat opened the door and I was immediately here.
Where? Are you at the front door?
I’ll come and open it for you.
No, I’m in the back.
Do you see anyone?
I don’t hear anything anymore.
Maybe you scared them off?
No, there’s no one out here. Just me, babe.
Mark, I can’t open the back door!
Shit.
What is it now?
I’m stuck.
What are you talking about? I can see you right there.
My feet. They’re stuck in the ground.
Okay, Mark. All of these games are getting old.
Babe, I’m serious. I literally can’t move.
It’s like I’m getting sucked into the ground.
Fuck, Mark. I can’t take this.
Call 911!
I can’t. I’ve been trying.
It’s like it’s blocked!
I can’t get through either!
Oh shit, what’s that?! I hear something again.
I don’t see anything, babe.
The windows in the kitchen.
Someone is rapping at them.
WTF.
Mark, come and get me. Please!
But be careful.
Ashley turns off the light.
Mark! Where are you?!
I don’t know what’s happening, babe.
I feel like I’m in quicksand.
When have you ever been in quicksand?
You know what I mean.
No, I don’t, because none of what you’re saying makes sense.
You were somehow transported to my house from the fraternity.
And now you’re supposedly stuck in my backyard.
While I sit here waiting for you in the dark with a possible creep outside waiting to attack me.
And it’s really starting to upset me, to be honest.
No one’s going to attack you, babe.
I’m right here.
Then come in and protect me!
Babe, I’m trying to.
I just don’t know what’s happening to me.
You’re being a creep is what’s happening.
I bet your new fraternity buddies have gotten you to come out here and play a trick on me.
And I think that’s really fucked up.
I never thought you would treat me like this.
What are you talking about, babe?
Don’t call me babe.
You’re being a piece of shit.
Like everyone else at this piece of shit school.
I just want to get the hell out of here.
I should have known you were too good to be true.
Stop it, Ashley.
I care so much about you.
I would never do anything to hurt you.
Then why are you doing this?
I swear to god, babe. You need to get help.
I’m really getting pulled into the ground.
I really don’t know what’s going on.
You have to trust me. Look out your window.
Oh my god, Mark.
What the hell is happening to you?
Grab on to something!
I’m trying to, babe.
Please, I need you.
You’re moving farther and farther away from me.
I can’t help it. I don’t know what it is but the pull is getting stronger and stronger.
Mark, you have to do something.
Pull yourself out of the ground!
I’m trying, Ashley. I don’t know if I’m strong enough, though.
Of course you are.
You are my everything.
I love you, babe.
Mark, I don’t know what I would do without you.
My life isn’t worth living if you’re not here with me.
Don’t say that.
It’s true.
No it’s not. You’re an amazing girl.
I’m going to come out and get you.
We’re in this together.
Oh my god. Mark, did you hear that?
No, what is it??
The front door…
Someone is pounding on it.
Oh fuck, Mark. This person won’t leave.
I don’t know what to do, Mark. I’m so scared.
I still can’t get through to the police.
What if they’re able to get in?
Hide!
Where?
Go in the closet.
I’m going to free myself and see what’s going on.
But I don’t want to lose sight of you.
Just be strong, babe. Like we always talk about.
If I go in the closet do you promise to stay with me?
Yes, of course!
I’ll be here.
We’re going to make it out of this.
Okay, I trust you.
Just come and save me.
Please.
Mark, what is going on??
This sound. I can’t fucking take it anymore.
Who the hell is trying to do this to me?
Babe, I’m almost down to my waist!
Screw this, I’m going to come and get you.
What about the person at the front door??
I’ll just climb out the window.
Okay, be careful though. We don’t know what’s going on with the ground.
It’s literally eating me alive.
I’d rather die with you than die alone.
You’re not alone. I’m right here with you.
Mark, oh shit, shit, shit.
The door! Oh fuck, it just came down!
Oh god, they’re coming in.
Mark, please don’t let this happen to me…
Hurry, babe. Open the window!
It’s not opening!!
It’s fucking stuck! Like the door!
Oh lord. Stop!
Oh, god, no.
Ashley, talk to me?
A piercing scream can be heard inside.
Babe, talk to me??
Oh my god, Ashley. Please tell me you’re okay.
What just happened?
Oh no, no, no. Please god.
I’ll never forgive myself if you’re…
I can’t even say it.
From inside the house, a bloody hand grasps at the cold window pane.
I’m hurt, Mark…
I need you…
This can’t be.
Shit.
This is what happened in the Red Room.
Happened?
Yes, you were stabbed in the stomach and bleeding just like you are now.
Oh god. Please…
Mark, I’m coming to you. We’re going to be together finally.
Fifteen minutes later, Ashley crawls through the backyard.
She clutches her wounded stomach with one hand and her cellphone with the other.
Mark, where are you?
Please don’t do this to me. Where are you?!
Ashley.
I don’t know…
I was sucked down into the ground and…
My eyes are just coming into focus.
I can’t see anything, but…
But what!?
Myself.
